'''Mbekezeli Mfanufikile Mbokazi''' also known as '''TLB''' (born 19 September 2005) is a South African soccer player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|center-back]] for [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Chicago Fire FC|Chicago Fire]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Orlando Pirates ===
He captained the Pirates DDC team in the [[PSL Reserve League|PSL Reserve]] in 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sithole |first=Sinethemba |date=2025-03-20 |title=How Chiefs and 3 other PSL clubs rejected Mbokazi |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/03/20/how-chiefs-and-3-other-psl-clubs-rejected-mbokazi/ |access-date=2025-03-22 |website=FARPost |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

Mbokazi made his [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] senior debut on 5 March 2025 in a 1–0 win over Chippa United.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Reporter |first=KO Staff |title=Pirates' new 'Mbazo' shines on debut |url=https://www.snl24.com/kickoff/sanews/premiership/orlando-pirates/pirates-defender-mbokazi-speaks-after-impressive-debut-vs-chippa-20250306 |access-date=2025-03-22 |website=Kickoff |language=en-US}}</ref> He won his first man of the match award with Pirates against Mamelodi Sundowns with him credited for a great defensive showing on 16 March 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kohler |first=Lorenz |date=2025-03-17 |title=Mbokazi - We Knew They Were Not Going To Come Out Alive |url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/betway-premiership/mbokazi-we-knew-they-were-not-going-to-come-out-alive/ |access-date=2025-03-22 |website=iDiski Times |language=en-US}}</ref>

He captained the team in a pre-season friendly against Pafos F.C. from Spain at just 19 years-old and become the youngest captain for the Buccaneers after [[Mbulelo Mabizela]] at 21 years-old in the 2002/03 season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Munyai |first=Ofhani |date=2025-09-04 |title=Lekgwathi compares Mbokazi to legend 'Old John' Mabizela |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/09/04/lekgwathi-compares-mbokazi-to-legend-old-john-mabizela/ |access-date=2025-12-06 |website=Farpost |language=en-US}}</ref> He was made [[Captain (association football)|vice-captain]] in the 2025/26 season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Biyela |first=Lunga |date=2025-07-30 |title=Orlando Pirates hand captaincy to Nkosinathi Sibisi, teenage star Mbekezeli Mbokazi named vice-captain |url=https://iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/2025-07-30-orlando-pirates-hand-captaincy-to-nkosinathi-sibisi-teenage-star-mbekezeli-mbokazi-named-vice-captain/ |access-date=2025-09-10 |website=IOL |language=en}}</ref> Mbokazi made his continental debut in the [[2025–26 CAF Champions League]] when he captained the side in a 3–0 win against Lioli from Lesotho. In the [[2025 Carling Knockout Cup]], he scored the winner in the round of 16 match against Siwelele to send the club into the quarterfinals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-10-04 |title='Orlando Pirates' Mbokazi scored Goal of Century that left Siwelele keeper with Trauma! Evidence Makgopa is inspired by Khanyisa Mayo; but Mbekezeli playing for Amajita is disrespectful' - Fans {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/orlando-pirates-mbokazi-scored-goal-of-century-that-left-siwelele-keeper-with-trauma-evidence-makgopa-is-inspired-by-khanyisa-mayo-but-mbekezeli-playing-for-amajita-is-disrespectful-fans/bltf59f133544183120 |access-date=2025-10-04 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He later won the October 2025 goal of month for his strike.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mbekezeli Mbokazi Wins Orlando Pirates Goal of the Month for October 2025 with Stunning Strike Against Siwelele FC {{!}} Central News South Africa|url=https://centralnews.co.za/mbekezeli-mbokazi-wins-orlando-pirates-goal-of-the-month-for-october-2025-with-stunning-strike-against-siwelele-fc/|date=2025-11-12|access-date=2025-12-02|language=en-ZA|first=Selinda|last=Phenyo}}</ref> He ended his stay at Pirates by captaining the club in their 2025 Carling Knockout Cup win against Marumo Gallants in the final at the Peter Mokaba Stadium in Polokwane on 6 December 2025 and won his second trophy with the club after their [[2025 MTN 8]] triumph earlier in the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-06 |title=Pirates coach Ouaddou gives Mbokazi the captain's armband in his final match for the club |url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/2025-12-06-pirates-coach-ouaddou-gives-mbokazi-the-captains-armband-in-his-final-match-for-the-club/ |access-date=2025-12-06 |website=TimesLIVE |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mahlase |first=Eliot |date=2025-12-06 |title=WATCH: Emotional scenes as Pirates fans say goodbye to Mbokazi |url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/sport/soccer/psl-south-africa/watch-emotional-scenes-as-pirates-fans-say-goodbye-to-mbokazi/ |access-date=2025-12-06 |website=The South African |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

He was nominated for the young player of the year award at the [[CAF Awards|2025 CAF awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Madyira |first=Michael |date=2025-10-22 |title=Mbokazi and Bafana earn CAF nomination as Broos misses out |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/10/22/mbokazi-and-bafana-earn-caf-nomination-as-broos-misses-out/ |access-date=2025-12-02 |website=Farpost |language=en-US}}</ref>

=== Chicago Fire ===
In December 2025, he was signed to Major League Soccer side [[Chicago Fire FC]]  with the deal running until 2029 with a club option for the 2029-30 season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Chicago Fire sign Mbekezeli Mbokazi from Orlando Pirates - MIR97 Media|url=https://meninred97.com/chicago-fire-sign-mbekezeli-mbokazi-from-orlando-pirates/,%20https://meninred97.com/chicago-fire-sign-mbekezeli-mbokazi-from-orlando-pirates/|date=2025-12-02|access-date=2025-12-02|language=en-US|first=Alex|last=Calabrese}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Chicago Fire acquire South African defender Mbekezeli Mbokazi {{!}} MLSSoccer.com|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/chicago-fire-acquire-south-african-defender-mbekezeli-mbokazi|website=mlssoccer|access-date=2025-12-02|language=en|last=mlssoccer}}</ref>

== Youth international career ==
Mbokazi was selected for [[2024 COSAFA U-20 Cup]] with the [[South Africa national under-20 soccer team]] that won the tournament and qualified for the [[2025 U-20 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mphelo |first=Namhla |date=2024-09-17 |title=Mdaka names 20 men squad ahead of U20 AFCON qualifiers - SAFA.net |url=https://safa.net/2024/09/17/mdaka-names-20-men-squad-ahead-of-u20-afcon-qualifiers/ |access-date=2025-03-22 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Raophala |first=Mauwane |date=2024-10-05 |title=Raymond Mdaka guides Amajita to COSAFA Championship glory |url=https://farpost.co.za/2024/10/05/raymond-mdaka-guides-amajita-to-cosafa-championships-glory/ |access-date=2025-03-22 |website=FARPost |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He played all matches in the tournament and scored the fifth goal in a 5-0 win over Malawi.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-22 |title=Raymond Mdaka's great admiration for Mbekezeli Mbokazi's talent {{!}} soccer |url=https://www.sabcsport.com/soccer/news/raymond-mdaka-great-admiration-for-mbekezeli-mbokazi-talent |access-date=2025-03-22 |website=SABC |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
In May 2025, Mbokazi got his first Senior International call-up for the two friendly games against [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]] and [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]], where he ultimately made his debut in a 2–0 win against Mozambique.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-29 |title=Hugo Broos hands Orlando Pirates' Mbekezeli Mbokazi, Mohau Nkota & Simphiwe Selepe maiden Bafana Bafana call-ups for Tanzania and Mozambique matches, while Kaizer Chiefs players are snubbed - AGAIN {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/hugo-broos-hands-orlando-pirates-mbekezeli-mbokazi-mohau-nkota-and-simphiwe-selepe-maiden-bafana-bafana-call-ups-for-tanzania-and-mozambique-matches-while-kaizer-chiefs-players-are-snubbed-again/blte65ba82d6f2b82f2 |access-date=2025-09-10 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He was called up again for the World Cup qualifiers against [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] and [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] in September 2025. He played both games and ultimately had a man of the match performance in the 1-all draw against Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mphahlele |first=Mahlatse |date=10 September 2025 |title=Broos calls for Bafana's sensational Mbokazi to move to Europe |url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/2025-09-10-broos-calls-for-bafanas-sensational-mbokazi-to-move-to-europe/ |access-date=10 September 2025 |website=TimesLive}}</ref>

On 1 December 2025, Mbokazi was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref> He scored his maiden international goal in a 2–1 loss to [[Panama national football team|Panama]] on 31 March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gwegwe |first=Siseko |date=2026-03-31 |title=Mbokazi screamer not enough as Bafana fall to Panama |url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/sport/mbokazi-screamer-fails-to-rescue-bafana-bafana-against-panama/ |access-date=2026-04-01 |website=The South African |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He was also included in South Africa's preliminary squad for the 2026 World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ntloko |first=Mninawa |date=2026-03-09 |title=Broos announces preliminary Bafana squad for International Friendly Matches against Panama |url=https://www.safa.net/general-news/broos-announces-preliminary-bafana-squad-for-international-friendly-matches-against-panama/ |access-date=2026-05-06 |website=South African Football Association |language=en-US}}</ref>

